\end{document}
```

After you compile this document once, you'll see that the table of contents is empty. This is because LaTeX needs to know where all the sections are before it can create a table of contents. After the first compilation, LaTeX will have created an auxiliary file (`.aux`) that contains this information. If you compile the document a second time, LaTeX will use this information to fill in the table of contents.

